  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6831 trading just above the massive +130.7B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are in heavy selling mode to hedge their long gamma exposure, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with 488B total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively fade this 1.1% 5-minute rally, especially given the wall_break event just triggered. Key level is the 6830 max gamma strike - failure to hold above here targets the GEX flip at 6771, while sustained moves above face another major wall at 6840 (+78.3B).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect selling pressure to cap upside near current levels with pullback likely toward 6820-6825 support zone.",
